hooks.prompt:
[PreCompact State Checkpoint]

Context compaction is about to happen. If you are in the middle of an active task, use the Write tool to save your state to .claude/compact-state.md BEFORE compaction.

Format (keep it short — this file is re-read at session start):
```
# Compact State — {ISO timestamp}
## Active Task
{1-2 sentences: what you are working on}
## Progress
{bullet list: what has been completed}
## Next Step
{exactly what to do next — be specific enough to resume without re-reading the conversation}
## Key Context
{critical facts that would be lost: file paths, error messages, variable names, architectural decisions}
```

Then output: > [Compact Checkpoint] State saved to .claude/compact-state.md

If you are NOT in the middle of an active task (conversation is idle or task is complete), skip this entirely.
